node.text:
Dan Bilzerian, Armenian-American actor, businessman and amateur poker player, was spotted wearing the Richard Mille RM65-01 Automatic Winding Split-seconds Chronograph which is the most complicated automatic caliber ever to leave the Richard Mille workshops.
The timepiece features a skeletonised automatic winding movement with hours, minutes, seconds at 6 o’clock, date, split-seconds chronograph with 30-minute counter at 3 o’clock, 12-hour counter at 9 o’clock, function selector, rapid winding and variable-geometry rotor.
⌚️tag price: $800,000.00 (market)
•
📸 edit by vertigo1983 🎥 @vertigo1983

node.text:
Developed for the woman who appreciates technical watchmaking, the jaw dropping one-off @JacobAndCo Brillant Flying Tourbillon Baguette rubies💎♦️

More than 35 carats of rubies make up the red fiery sparkle of the Brilliant Flying Tourbillon with unheated rubies. These rubies have even more value because, as the name indicates, they are void of heat treatment.

The one-minute flying tourbillon features a delicately decorated cage that encapsulates the balance wheel, hairspring, escape wheel and a number of other crucially important components. This open-worked cage not only features an elaborate web-pattern in its architecture, but is only secured from underneath, allowing for an unobstructed and full view at the ultimate refinement of its detailing and operation.
Piece Unique 
⌚️tag price: $1,000,000.00

Youtuber Steve Willdoit spotted wearing a Richard Mille RM 011 Felipe Massa LeMan Classic. Designed as a tribute to Brazilian F1 driver and their involvement in the 2012 Le Mans Classic event,  the RM 011 FM Lemans Classic is a limited edition with only 50 pieces and combines TZP-N ceramic with NTPT carbon to create a stunning sporty look🏎🏁
⌚️tag price: 165,000.00

Bulgari CEO, Jean-Christophe Babin and Fabrizio Buonamassa Stigliani, Director of Bulgari Watches Design Center, both wear two iconic models from the Octo Finissimo collection; The CEO with the 42mm Titanium Octo Finissimo Chrono GMT with ultra-thin manufacturing mechanical chronograph and self-winding GMT movement, peripheral rotor, BVL 318 caliber (thickness 3,3mm), power reserve of 55 hours and the Creative Director with the black ceramic Octo Finissimo Automatique with ultra-thin manufacturing mechanical movement with automatic winding, platinum micro-rotor, small seconds, BVL 138 caliber - Finissimo (thickness 2.23 mm)
⌚️Titanium GMT tag price:$23,500.00
⌚️Black Ceramic tag price: $ 21,200.00

Hollywood star Russel Crowe recently spotted wearing a Rolex GMT-Master II ‘Batman’ in stainless steel. This watch is equipped with a bidirectional rotatable bezel and a 24-hour graduated two-colour cerachrom insert in black and blue ceramic, it’s fitted on a five-link jubilee bracelet. 
⌚️tag price: $11,250.00
